00:12:13,350 --> 00:12:17,950
If I'd been inside, Mr. Pacovsky, I couldn't have seen what I just saw.

271
00:12:20,350 --> 00:12:23,450
Is nobody going to ask me what I saw?

272
00:12:25,350 --> 00:12:27,150
I saw Iva with some guy.

273
00:12:27,230 --> 00:12:27,690
What?

274
00:12:28,450 --> 00:12:29,550
That he's a gynecologist.

275
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,050
I've seen him somewhere before.

276
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:34,340
Try to quickly remember where you saw him.

277
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,020
In a store?

278
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:35,780
On a tram?

279
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:36,660
At the gynecologist's.

280
00:12:37,650 --> 00:12:38,300
Lexa.

281
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:39,300
In prison?

282
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:41,060
Ozzak.

283
00:12:42,450 --> 00:12:43,550
Birthday party.

284
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,610
My birthday party.

285
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,950
A relative of yours?

286
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:47,930
Oh my God!

287
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:48,860
Oh my God!

288
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:50,820
Oh my God, speak, you unfortunate woman!

289
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:53,260
He was the stripper who jumped out of the cake at me.

290
00:12:53,650 --> 00:12:56,150
Like, completely naked?

291
00:12:56,450 --> 00:13:02,050
No, at first he had this police cap and a really big baton.

292
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:10,710
Tomas, wake up.

293
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:12,000
What is it, what is it?

294
00:13:12,080 --> 00:13:12,520
Was I sleeping?

295
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:16,750
Well, something like that.

296
00:13:19,050 --> 00:13:20,150
What a relief.

297
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:31,110
I dreamed that some boy invited Ivushka on a date to a sauna and then Marcelka came saying he's a stripper.

298
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:34,850
That wasn't a dream.

299
00:13:43,950 --> 00:13:46,150
That's practically a porn actor.

300
00:13:46,950 --> 00:13:51,050
And why couldn't Ivushka bring home a stripper?

301
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:52,930
They don't spend money on clothes.

302
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:58,850
He's out every night, so he doesn't need a bed, and we could use him to attract girls.

303
00:13:58,950 --> 00:14:02,390
And hasn't it occurred to you that it could be the other way around?

304
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:04,350
That he'd take her away?

305
00:14:06,350 --> 00:14:09,250
Mr. Pacovsky, am I understanding correctly that Iva has a boyfriend?

306
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:18,950
Wait, as in he'd take Ivushka away from us?

307
00:14:30,950 --> 00:14:32,450
Lex, what are you doing here?

308
00:14:33,350 --> 00:14:34,850
I borrowed keys from a buddy.

309
00:14:36,150 --> 00:14:38,350
Ozzak shouldn't have his own keys.

310
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,150
Sis, don't you want to leave?

311
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:42,640
She doesn't.

312
00:14:43,850 --> 00:14:45,250
Sis, at least turn around.

313
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:30,850
Have you ever seen anything like that?

314
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:32,540
I have.

315
00:15:32,650 --> 00:15:34,550
You were trying it all last night.

316
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:41,450
Dad's going crazy.

317
00:15:41,950 --> 00:15:44,750
He just took my phone and read your text message.

318
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:48,150
Man, if someone touched something of mine, they wouldn't survive it.

319
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:49,750
I'd have a blackout.

320
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:52,650
And when I have a blackout, I lose control.

321
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:54,750
But he didn't mean it badly.

322
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:56,850
He's just worried about me.

323
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:57,690
No comment.

324
00:15:57,950 --> 00:16:00,150
That's the big downside of still living with your dad.

325
00:16:00,550 --> 00:16:03,450
I was on my own feet right at eighteen.

326
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:07,950
But you're only twenty?

327
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:09,050
Well, almost.

328
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:14,250
Then it's high time, want to move in with me? I've got a place.

329
00:16:14,650 --> 00:16:16,320
Not really, not yet.

330
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:18,050
But I'll think about it.

331
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:22,350
Well, you know, who would take care of Dad and Uncle.

332
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:27,650
So Robert, what do you like to do?

333
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:30,750
I really love going to the gym.

334
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:34,050
Comes in handy at work all the time.

335
00:16:34,850 --> 00:16:35,950
So what do you do?

336
00:16:37,250 --> 00:16:40,160
I'd rather tell you once we get to know each other a bit better.

337
00:16:40,450 --> 00:16:41,250
You know how it is.

338
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:44,550
Why all this secrecy about your work?

339
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:46,850
Some people react to the job.

340
00:16:47,950 --> 00:16:50,750
I feel so much calmer when you put it like that.

341
00:16:50,850 --> 00:16:53,190
But it's nothing scary.

342
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:54,870
It's just that people have a lot of prejudice about us.

343
00:16:55,950 --> 00:16:58,850
Look, it's a job for real men.

344
00:16:59,450 --> 00:17:05,850
I need a fit body, strong nerves, endurance.

345
00:17:07,050 --> 00:17:08,950
Tonight I still have to go to work.

346
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,050
I've got my uniform with me.

347
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:13,690
I see.

348
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:22,670
Yesterday around this time I had a call at an apartment.

349
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:24,850
Some old woman was lying there.

350
00:17:25,050 --> 00:17:26,850
Not a pretty sight.

351
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:44,460
Tomas?

352
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,450
Mr. Pacovsky!

353
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,350
Ozzak!

354
00:18:02,410 --> 00:18:04,840
Ozzak, for God's sake, what's going on here?

355
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:06,160
Ivushka is leaving us.

356
00:18:06,520 --> 00:18:07,800
What, already today?

357
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:10,080
Today or tomorrow, a stripper or a teacher.

358
00:18:11,650 --> 00:18:14,640
Our little girl is gone and there's a grown woman in her place.

359
00:18:15,050 --> 00:18:17,650
And she'll leave us too, like all women.

360
00:18:17,850 --> 00:18:20,450
Don't worry, I won't leave you.

361
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:21,700
Never mind then.

362
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:28,820
Mr. Pacovsky, I have bad news and good news, which do you want to hear first?

363
00:18:29,050 --> 00:18:29,840
The bad news?

364
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:30,780
Is Iva dead?

365
00:18:31,550 --> 00:18:32,480
She's not dead.

366
00:18:32,850 --> 00:18:34,850
She went to the Jezevec for a date with the stripper.

367
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:36,650
Now the bad news.

368
00:18:36,670 --> 00:18:37,590
And the bad news is.

369
00:18:38,710 --> 00:18:40,370
Wait, Mr. Ozzak, now you've confused me.

370
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:41,650
That was the bad news.

371
00:18:42,750 --> 00:18:44,190
What's the good news, Lexa?

372
00:18:45,150 --> 00:18:47,050
Iva isn't into strippers at all.

373
00:18:47,450 --> 00:18:49,850
Really, I tested it on my own skin.

374
00:18:51,650 --> 00:18:52,550
A hundred percent.

375
00:18:52,950 --> 00:18:54,550
The guy is definitely hiding it from her.

376
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:57,230
When we expose him in front of her, she'll dump him.

377
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:58,050
Like she dumped me.

378
00:18:58,450 --> 00:19:02,450
I'm not entirely sure it's the stripper, though.

379
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:02,870
But...

380
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,920
But you said it was him when you saw him.

381
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:06,760
I saw him, but with clothes on.

382
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:12,480
And besides, at the birthday party I wasn't exactly looking at his face.

383
00:19:12,850 --> 00:19:13,840
Then where were you looking?

384
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:17,250
That doesn't matter at all.

385
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:22,850
Three things can come between Iva and sex, and I'm not one of them.

386
00:19:23,450 --> 00:19:26,650
Don't worry, I'll stand between Iva and sex.

387
00:19:28,550 --> 00:19:30,950
Right, let's go to Iva and tell her everything.

388
00:19:31,550 --> 00:19:32,650
We'll open her eyes.

389
00:19:32,850 --> 00:19:35,340
We'll expose the parasite that's latched onto her.

390
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:36,700
Of course, Lexa, let's go.

391
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,520
Us too.

392
00:19:37,820 --> 00:19:38,700
For God's sake, why me?

393
00:19:39,550 --> 00:19:40,660
For identification purposes.

394
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:41,950
Bro, you coming too?

395
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:44,350
So who's the better dad now, huh?

396
00:19:46,130 --> 00:19:46,450
Let's go.

397
00:20:00,250 --> 00:20:01,150
That's weak.

398
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,810
Hi, this is Tomas Pacovsky.

399
00:20:09,810 --> 00:20:10,650
Remember me?

400
00:20:11,450 --> 00:20:14,150
Yeah, would you have a minute?

401
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:23,040
I don't know.

402
00:20:23,250 --> 00:20:25,250
For God's sake, why did we bring you along?

403
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:29,250
He did have a distinguishing mark, but we can't see it from here.

404
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,620
Let's sit at a closer table then.

405
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:33,580
That won't help.

406
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:39,590
He had a tattoo on his butt.

407
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:41,150
So, a manly guy?

408
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:48,050
On the contrary, he was very manly.

409
00:20:48,460 --> 00:20:49,100
Too bad.

410
00:21:18,150 --> 00:21:19,550
You're a real friend.

411
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:22,380
I don't even know why I'm supporting you in this.

412
00:21:22,850 --> 00:21:25,250
You're just sitting here feeling sorry for yourself.

413
00:21:25,330 --> 00:21:26,250
Tomas, pull yourself together.

414
00:21:26,290 --> 00:21:27,670
Every trouble has its limit.

415
00:21:27,670 --> 00:21:31,010
But she's the only thing in my life I truly care about.

416
00:21:31,010 --> 00:21:32,930
Then do something about it.

417
00:21:32,930 --> 00:21:36,430
If you really care about her, you have to get moving.

418
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:37,730
You're a dad, so fight.

419
00:21:38,650 --> 00:21:39,550
You mean it?

420
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:42,450
Why give up the match at halftime?

421
00:21:43,150 --> 00:21:44,190
That was beautifully said.

422
00:21:44,450 --> 00:21:45,350
Yes, why indeed.

423
00:21:46,050 --> 00:21:47,350
And it even rhymes.

424
00:21:47,650 --> 00:21:48,650
See?

425
00:21:48,830 --> 00:21:50,370
I like you better like this.

426
00:21:50,490 --> 00:21:51,970
Yes, we need to go right away.

427
00:21:53,370 --> 00:21:54,390
Yeah, please.

428
00:21:55,250 --> 00:21:55,920
Aren't you hungry?

429
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:57,720
We've got sausage goulash in the oven.

430
00:22:02,650 --> 00:22:05,350
In what situations does an adult man take off his pants?

431
00:22:05,490 --> 00:22:08,050
They're about to pay, so probably soon behind the corner in the park.

432
00:22:08,810 --> 00:22:10,050
Mom, you have to think of something.

433
00:22:11,050 --> 00:22:11,610
I've got it.

434
00:22:12,050 --> 00:22:15,450
Mr. Ozzak will dress up as a doctor and go give him an injection.

435
00:22:19,850 --> 00:22:21,450
Do you see what I see?

436
00:22:24,450 --> 00:22:25,250
Good evening.

437
00:22:26,150 --> 00:22:28,350
I'm Tomas Pacovsky, father of Iva here.

438
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,340
What are you doing here?

439
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:32,350
Being a dad.

440
00:22:33,650 --> 00:22:34,650
Nice to meet you.

441
00:22:35,250 --> 00:22:42,750
I came to tell you that I don't approve of what you do for a living, and that you should have more decency and not get involved with decent and inexperienced girls.

442
00:22:42,950 --> 00:22:45,460
I don't do anything I should be ashamed of, Mr. Pacovsky.

443
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:46,660
And at home?

444
00:22:46,660 --> 00:22:48,950
What do they say about your profession?

445
00:22:49,250 --> 00:22:50,150
Mom's proud.

446
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:53,070
Well, you're quite a strange family.

447
00:22:53,070 --> 00:22:53,670
Excuse me?

448
00:22:53,930 --> 00:22:55,350
Dad, please, stop.

449
00:22:55,530 --> 00:22:57,550
Easy, Ivushka, this is between me and this gentleman.

450
00:22:57,790 --> 00:22:59,170
And me too.

451
00:22:59,510 --> 00:23:02,070
No stripper is going to take Ivushka away from us.

452
00:23:02,250 --> 00:23:03,350
You're a stripper?

453
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:04,820
I'm not.

454
00:23:05,370 --> 00:23:06,270
What kind of nonsense is that?

455
00:23:06,410 --> 00:23:06,750
But he is.

456
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:08,330
He jumped out of a cake for this lady.

457
00:23:08,390 --> 00:23:08,770
I...

458
00:23:10,250 --> 00:23:11,450
I'm not a stripper.

459
00:23:12,050 --> 00:23:13,050
Prove it.

460
00:23:13,460 --> 00:23:15,540
I'm supposed to prove I'm not a stripper?

461
00:23:15,820 --> 00:23:16,700
Take off your pants.

462
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:19,060
That would prove I am a stripper, wouldn't it?

463
00:23:19,910 --> 00:23:21,130
That's true, Ozzak.

464
00:23:21,130 --> 00:23:22,950
Why should he take off his pants?

465
00:23:23,690 --> 00:23:24,170
Because...

466
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:27,950
Where does he have it?

467
00:23:28,350 --> 00:23:29,250
Right here.

468
00:23:30,510 --> 00:23:30,990
Ew.

469
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:33,550
What's going on?

470
00:23:34,050 --> 00:23:36,450
I'm asking you as the father of my daughter.

471
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:38,880
Take off your pants so we know where we stand.

472
00:23:39,440 --> 00:23:40,620
Are you all crazy?

473
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,760
Fine, differently then.

474
00:23:43,650 --> 00:23:44,860
Ozzak, hold him.

475
00:23:45,850 --> 00:23:52,150
That's me.

476
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:53,950
You'll see.

477
00:23:55,790 --> 00:23:56,910
It's him!

478
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:05,420
Robert, please, don't be mad at them.

479
00:24:05,650 --> 00:24:07,150
You've got a pretty crazy family.

480
00:24:07,750 --> 00:24:12,450
You should decide whether you'll come with me, or keep rotting here with these nutjobs.

481
00:24:12,550 --> 00:24:14,250
That last punch too.

482
00:24:14,550 --> 00:24:16,250
Just don't have a blackout, okay?

483
00:24:20,650 --> 00:24:22,950
To serve and protect.

484
00:24:28,850 --> 00:24:30,650
Do they bring oranges to prison?

485
00:24:31,650 --> 00:24:33,250
Lexa has an allergy, I think.

486
00:24:33,650 --> 00:24:35,200
He can peel them then.

487
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:36,980
And what do I have to bring him?

488
00:24:37,250 --> 00:24:38,350
When I go visit him.

489
00:24:38,850 --> 00:24:40,750
And what if you run into Robert there?

490
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:42,550
Robert is an idiot.

491
00:24:43,530 --> 00:24:45,870
I'm glad you're saying that, Ivushka.

492
00:24:46,090 --> 00:24:48,890
You know, I'd have killed you if you kept dating him.

493
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:51,950
I know, I didn't behave well either, but you were worried about me.

494
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:56,430
But now I know I'll never tell you who you should or shouldn't date.

495
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:57,210
That's your life.

496
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:01,750
How could you let him call us a family of nutjobs?

497
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:07,470
Come on, in protest let's chain ourselves to the railing outside the precinct.

498
00:25:07,850 --> 00:25:12,050
Count me out, last time we did that, it poured for two months.

499
00:25:14,550 --> 00:25:16,320
Yeah, but we have to do something.

500
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:19,950
Imagine Lexa being afraid to bend over in the shower for the soap.

501
00:25:21,550 --> 00:25:24,550
Well I'll be, you got busted too.

502
00:25:24,950 --> 00:25:26,420
We're going to chain ourselves to the railing.

503
00:25:26,850 --> 00:25:28,760
Haven't had pneumonia in a while, have you?

504
00:25:29,150 --> 00:25:32,350
In protest against the unjust imprisonment of your son Lexa.

505
00:25:32,650 --> 00:25:34,950
Lexa assaulted a police officer.

506
00:25:35,390 --> 00:25:35,870
In self-defense.

507
00:25:35,870 --> 00:25:39,050
Doesn't matter, when you kick a cop, they always haul you in.

508
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:42,520
I think what pissed Robert off the most was that he couldn't catch Lexa afterward.

509
00:25:42,660 --> 00:25:42,820
Yeah.

510
00:25:42,920 --> 00:25:44,620
And that he threw his gun into the juice.

511
00:25:45,750 --> 00:25:47,050
He really shouldn't have spit in his face.

512
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:49,460
A chip off the old block.

513
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,160
I protest.

514
00:25:51,280 --> 00:25:52,520
Something has to be done about this.

515
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:53,750
My thoughts exactly.

516
00:25:54,350 --> 00:25:55,230
Good evening.

517
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:55,850
Hey, Mom.

518
00:25:56,210 --> 00:25:56,690
Hey.

519
00:25:57,350 --> 00:25:59,590
Lexa, they let you out already?

520
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:00,070
Yeah.

521
00:26:00,870 --> 00:26:02,910
I fixed their network and cleaned viruses off their computers.

522
00:26:02,930 --> 00:26:06,090
And I installed a card game for the chief, so he wanted us to be on first-name terms.

523
00:26:06,250 --> 00:26:08,230
He even gave me an application to join the force.

524
00:26:08,350 --> 00:26:09,690
Don't you dare.

525
00:26:10,450 --> 00:26:11,970
What would people say?

526
00:26:11,970 --> 00:26:14,730
Robert would be especially thrilled.

527
00:26:14,950 --> 00:26:15,870
Robert's in trouble.

528
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:17,250
Apparently it wasn't the first time.

529
00:26:17,350 --> 00:26:19,750
Uncle chief said they're going to fire him.

530
00:26:21,410 --> 00:26:22,330
Dude.

531
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:25,070
Stop it, or I'm going to cry.

532
00:26:25,450 --> 00:26:26,850
Alright, take care, jailbird.

533
00:26:27,050 --> 00:26:28,090
We need to find Sasha.

534
00:26:28,450 --> 00:26:30,330
You think she can just disappear whenever she feels like it?

535
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:30,810
Shall we go?

536
00:26:32,350 --> 00:26:33,500
